Will setupOutputAndPolicy(bool blocking) and setupOutputAndPolicy(mode & ANDROID_LOG_NONBLOCK) make you happier for this moment? If not, I will split it.

Splitting this into two functions is clearer from one maintenance perspective, but the pair of functions would _still_ need to be called in tight sequence; moving one or the other around (and if you look at the patch set in this series, this is happening) and thus introduces maintenance risk. As soon as we consider opening the output file, we want to drop to background cgroup.

I may wish to reconsider this, maybe it is better to set the priority just before we _really_ start reading, rather than when we decide to open the output file for writing? (my answer will come when I respin this CL in the patch series)

The background cgroup policy is closely tied to where/what the input is coming from and where the output is going, and controls the flow rate of the input and output.

FYI the mode argument is actually representing the _input_ mode.

